        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Hardly any lvl 60 necro even has Funeral Pyre on my server. Only a few guilds are capable of taking down the mob that drops it. Also from what I hear this mob can drop various class spells. So what is the chance of Funeral Pyre even dropping off this mob in Ssraa? Very slim.</P><P>One of the lvl 60 necros I know in Legacy of Steel doesn't even have Funeral Pyre yet. That speaks volumes. If a uber guilded lvl 60 necro doesn't even have it, what chance do the rest of us have? Zero. That spell doesn't even come up for sale and I monitor our trade channel constantly. You'd need an armoured car to load the plat even if it did come up for sale.</P><P>Let's take Velious and necro spells. After 1 month of release, I had all of the mob dropped Velious necros spells. Every single damn one. Now Velious was supposed to be the "guild raid" expansion. Verant promised us that Luclin was going to be more "group" oriented so why is it that I do not know one single necro on our server that even has Funeral Pyre?</P><P>Finally, there's a certain group of necros that continually post on this website and they use Funeral Pyre as part of thier DPS calculations. This spell may as well be an Ancient Spell as far as I'm concerned because 99.9% of lvl 60 necromancers do not have it. Trying to misrepresent the power of a lvl 60 necromancer by using Funeral Pyre is misleading and damaging to our class.</P><P>The idea that certain spells should only drop from certain spells is a bad one. Someone at Verant thought this was a clever idea, but it's proved catastrophic for casters. At least in Kunark and in Velious all lvl 60 mobs can drop any lvl 60 spell. With Luclin only a select few guilds will be able to ever get these spells and then this leads to pharming and keeps other guilds out. </P><P>Verant it's time to make lvl 60 spells drop off of any lvl 60+ mob. Anything less is unfair and unacceptable. Verant you want casters to be balanced? Then put your money where your mouth is and fix the drop rates and put these spells on a universal drop table for uber mobs. Thank you.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
