         Funeral Pyre is on my list of spells to get. Rhag2 is not a difficult mob to kill at all but the simple fact of it is that because there is only one mob that drops the spell the mob is constantly camped.</P><P>As Dornette said this is a idiotic design element but VI.</P><P>Why VI does really stupid garbage like that is beyond me. There is already far to much contention for the high end mobs without VI adding to the queue of people trying to get a spell they actually need in order to fulfill their duty.</P><P>I have witnessed races between high end guilds for these special mobs more times than I care to remember. The "races" do not lead to friendly competition they lead to backbiting and complete and utter b/s as the guilds actively do their best to ensure that they get the mob in question.</P><P>Does this make the **GAME** more enjoyable to play? Not for me. I play EQ becuase it is an interactive game. I do not play on a PvP server as PvP has absolutely no attraction for me. I thourougly dislike "design elements" that reduce the enjoyability of the **GAME**. One such design element is creating artificial contention for rare drops by restricting the drop to a single mob with a long repop time.</P><P>As to the group aego and group C3. Verant have stated numerous times that they favor clerics and enchanters. These spells are "necessary for the high end game to reduce downtime". So they are common drops. That is so blatantly unfair it is not even funny.</P><P>Regarding the drop rate of Funeral Pyre. An incredibly talented guild on Luclin has killed Rhag2 15 times, Funeral Pyre has dropped 3 times for them. Do the math and you will see how long it will be before the majority of high end necros ever see this spell.</P><P>Yet people always assume that our DPS includes FP. Face facts:-</P><P>1/ there are very few people with FP.<BR>2/ the resist rates on our spells are way higher than for any other class, I get really pissed off when, as a level 60 necro, I can't land a Pyrocuror on a high end "fire susceptible mob" yet a level 50 magician's fire based nukes all hit. I can't land Splurt on a mob, yet the enchanter equivalent POS dot lands with no trouble at all.</P><P>I guess we as necros should be thankful that at least the totally insane agro our spells cause has been reduced somewhat (Ouch did I just ask VI for a retro nerf by mentioning that?).</P><P>But you know what? I'm not grateful at all. Our class has been treated like crap by VI. They constantly nerf us and almost never give us anything to improve or bring our class back into line with the the other caster classes. VI slaps us in the face by totally ignoring the major issue with our class, dot stacking, and then goes back to "balancing clerics".</P><P>I am a fair person. I am really sick of being treated unfairly by the powers that be at VI.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
