        &nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_messengers.asp?mode=AIM&amp;AIM=bronstahd&amp;M_NAME=Karae')"><img src="icon_aim.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Send Karae an instant message" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=50869&amp;TOPIC_ID=5551&amp;FORUM_ID=6&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&amp;Topic_Title=Group+DMF+and+Funeral+pyre&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Funeral Pyre is fine. EVERY caster class has to deal with the same thing in Luclin, you seem to be missing this point. Funeral Pyre is actually one of the more easily obtained spells. At least it doesn't drop off of Emperor Ssra like Garrison's Superior Sundering. ;) In any event, this spell drops fairly often; I'm sure you can find someone selling it at the very least. I believe we have several copies for sale on Veeshan.</P><P>Dead Men Floating and Gangrenous Touch of Zum`uul...who knows what the fuck Verant was thinking. I get the feeling there are fewer than 10 copies of each, serverwide. They're just disgustingly rare. IMO these should have been vendor spells. At the least they should be random drops of any mob in Chardok, not the rarest drop off a rare mob. Of course, if it came down to being able to obtain these spells or having dots stacking, class AA's reworked, pets upgraded...I'd be happy never seeing either of these spells. ;)</P><P>yeah</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183135" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183135</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
